        </code>
        <p>Use the above URL in your og:image meta tag. You can also dynamically or manually generate these links using the following schema:</p>
        <code>
          https://og-image.xyz/og/:title/:subtitle/:url/:protocol/:font/:image/:color/data.png
        </code>
        <br>
        <details>
          <summary>Details</summary>
          <table>
            <tr>
              <th>Parameter</th>
              <th>Notes</th>
              <th>Options</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>:title</td>
              <td>The title, largest text in the image. You can use "{{n}}" for a newline</td>
              <td>N/A</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>:subtitle</td>
              <td>The subtitle, under the largest text. You can use "{{n}}" for a newline</td>
              <td>N/A</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>:url</td>
              <td>The url you want to show at the bottom. This should be without the protocol (http://). You cannot use slashes here, but you CAN use "{{s}}"</td>
              <td>og-image.xyz, jackcrane.rocks</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>:protocol</td>
              <td>The protocol of the aformentioned URL. Should not include "://"</td>
              <td>http, https, file</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>:font</td>
              <td>The font you want used in the image. You must use one of the fonts we support (supported fonts in examples)</td>
              <td>menlo, atkinson</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>:image</td>
              <td>The image you want to be used as the background. You must use one of the images we support (supported images in examples)</td>
              <td>candybar, cheerfulorange, renownedred, unmatchedeclipse, virtualshapes, flawlessaffinity, prettyheroic, irritablehero, circleacquired, descendsun, shatteredfeelings</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>:color</td>
              <td>The hex code of the color you want as the foreground. You cannot use the pound (#) symbol, so use {{h}} instead.</td>
              <td>{{h}}FF6600</td>
            </tr>
          </table>
        </details>
